# WHAT IS globby AND WHY IS IT THE 68TH TS-NODE CLI LIBRARY?
#
# globby (https://github.com/sindresorhus/globby, 2,643+ stars) is
# **Sindre Sorhus's "user-friendly glob matching"** — a higher-
# level Node.js glob library that wraps fast-glob (R639) with
# gitignore-awareness + expand-directories + iterator API + auto-
# cwd detection.  Where fast-glob is the FAST CORE ENGINE, globby
# is the USER-FRIENDLY FRONTEND.
#
# globby's distinguishing characteristics:
#
#   1. HIGH-LEVEL WRAPPER OVER fast-glob — globby uses fast-glob
#      internally as its core engine, adding conveniences that
#      fast-glob deliberately leaves out:
#
#          import { globby } from 'globby';
#
#          // Basic usage (auto-handles cwd, returns array):
#          const files = await globby(['**/*.js']);
#
#          // With gitignore awareness (NOT in fast-glob):
#          const files = await globby(['**/*.js'], {
#              gitignore: true,  // reads .gitignore automatically
#          });
#
#          // With ignore-file support (NOT in fast-glob):
#          const files = await globby(['**/*.js'], {
#              ignoreFiles: ['.gitignore', '.gptlintignore'],
#          });
#
#          // With expand-directories (NOT in fast-glob default):
#          const files = await globby(['src'], {
#              expandDirectories: true,
#                // ↑ "src" automatically becomes "src/**/*"
#          });
#
#          // Iterator API for memory-bounded large trees:
#          for await (const file of globbyStream(['**/*.ts'])) {
#              console.log(file);
#          }
#
#      Compare:
#         * fast-glob (R639): RAW glob engine, no gitignore
#         * Node node-glob: similar but slower than fast-glob
#         * Node micromatch: pattern-matching only (no filesystem)
#         * Rust ignore (BurntSushi): similar gitignore wrapper
#                                       over walkdir (R641)
#         * Go bmatcuk/doublestar (R642): direct ** matching
#         * globby: HIGH-LEVEL WRAPPER over fast-glob with
#                    gitignore + ignore-files + expand-directories
#                    + iterator
#      FIRST documented Node.js Axis 14 library that EXPLICITLY
#      wraps a lower-level glob engine (fast-glob) with developer-
#      friendly conveniences.
#
#   2. GITIGNORE-AWARE BY DEFAULT — globby's `gitignore: true`
#      option triggers automatic .gitignore + .ignore + parent-
#      directory ignore-file discovery:
#
#          // Read .gitignore + .ignore files automatically:
#          const sourceFiles = await globby(['**/*.ts'], {
#              gitignore: true,
#                // ↑ walks up from cwd looking for .gitignore
#                //   files, reads them, applies their patterns
#                //   to filter output
#          });
#
#          // The behavior is equivalent to:
#          //   git ls-files --others --exclude-standard | grep '\.ts$'
#          // (i.e. files that git would consider untracked but
#          //  not ignored, filtered by glob pattern)
#
#      Compare:
#         * fast-glob (R639): NO gitignore awareness (raw glob)
#         * Rust ignore (BurntSushi): similar — wraps walkdir
#                                       with gitignore
#         * Go src-d/go-git: separate gitignore parsing
#         * Go bmatcuk/doublestar (R642): NO gitignore (raw glob)
#         * Node node-glob: NO gitignore awareness
#         * globby: BUILT-IN gitignore via { gitignore: true }
#      FIRST documented Node.js Axis 14 library with built-in
#      .gitignore reading + multi-level ignore-file discovery.
#
#   3. EXPAND-DIRECTORIES — when passed a bare directory path,
#      globby automatically expands it to all files within:
#
#          // Without expand-directories (fast-glob behavior):
#          await fastGlob(['src']);  // → ['src'] (just the dir)
#
#          // With globby's expand-directories (default true):
#          await globby(['src']);    // → ['src/foo.ts', 'src/bar.ts', ...]
#
#          // With custom file extension filtering:
#          await globby(['src', 'tests'], {
#              expandDirectories: {
#                  extensions: ['ts', 'tsx'],
#                  files: ['*.test.ts'],  // additional patterns
#              },
#          });
#
#      Compare:
#         * fast-glob (R639): bare directory returns just the directory
#         * Node node-glob: requires explicit `/**/*` suffix
#         * Rust walkdir (R641): traverses directories anyway
#         * Go afero.Walk (R638): traverses anyway
#         * globby: AUTO-EXPAND bare directories to file patterns
#      FIRST documented Node.js Axis 14 library with auto-
#      expand-directories convenience.
#
#   4. ISGITIGNORED + ISIGNOREDBYIGNOREFILES HELPERS — globby
#      exports standalone helpers for arbitrary ignore-file
#      processing:
#
#          import { isGitIgnored, isIgnoredByIgnoreFiles } from 'globby';
#
#          // Check if a specific path is gitignored:
#          const isIgnored = await isGitIgnored({ cwd: process.cwd() });
#          if (isIgnored('src/secrets.ts')) {
#              console.log('This file is gitignored');
#          }
#
#          // Check against arbitrary ignore files:
#          const isIgnoredCustom = await isIgnoredByIgnoreFiles(
#              '.dockerignore'
#          );
#          if (isIgnoredCustom('node_modules')) {
#              // ...
#          }
#
#      These helpers are useful in build tools that need to
#      verify ignore-file behavior without doing a full glob run.
#      Compare:
#         * fast-glob (R639): no such helpers (raw engine)
#         * Rust ignore (BurntSushi): similar Walk::is_path_ignored
#         * Go: requires manual .gitignore parsing
#         * globby: EXPORTED standalone ignore-check helpers
#      FIRST documented Node.js Axis 14 library with exported
#      ignore-check standalone helpers.
#
#   5. SINDRE SORHUS / CHALK-ORG / 4-LIBRARY ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE
#      — globby is by Sindre Sorhus (sindresorhus on GitHub),
#      author of ~1500+ npm packages.  With R643, Sindre becomes
#      the SECOND library-author with FOUR documented headline
#      libraries in the taxonomy:
#         * boxen (Axis 7 / Box Drawing — R600 _wtfjs)
#         * wrap-ansi (Axis 12 / Text Wrapping — R627 _bundown,
#                       chalk-org maintained)
#         * conf (Axis 13 / Configuration Files — R635 _linky)
#         * globby (Axis 14 / Paths / Filesystem — R643 THIS)
#      Plus extensive transitive documentation via chalk + ora +
#      cli-table3 (chalk-org) + execa + got + pretty-bytes +
#      pretty-ms + env-paths + update-notifier + ~1500 more
#      packages.  Downstream globby users:
#         * nexe/nexe (13.5k stars — single-binary Node)
#         * chakra-ui/ark (5k stars — UI components)
#         * JamieMason/ImageOptim-CLI (3.5k stars)
#         * histoire-dev/histoire (3.5k stars — Vite story playground)
#         * vuejs/vue-codemod (Vue migration scripts)
#         * sysgears/mochapack (Mocha + webpack)
#         * ranyitz/qnm (node_modules query tool)
#         * vtex/toolbelt (VTEX e-commerce CLI)
#         * rasshofer/yaml-lint (YAML linter)
#         * gptlint/gptlint (THIS — LLM-powered linter)
#         * sindresorhus/cpy (Sindre's own cp replacement)
#         * vladshcherbin/rollup-plugin-copy (Rollup plugin)
#         * Many Rollup/Vite/esbuild plugins
#         * 5000+ Node.js build tools
#      FIRST documented Node.js Axis 14 library with this
#      specific Sindre-Sorhus four-library + chalk-org
#      foundational ecosystem provenance.
#
# globby's relationship to fast-glob (R639) and other Axis 14
# libraries:
#
#   * Unlike fast-glob (R639, Node) — fast-glob is RAW GLOB
#                                       ENGINE (no gitignore,
#                                       no expand-directories);
#                                       globby WRAPS fast-glob
#                                       with developer
#                                       conveniences
#   * Closest cross-language analogs:
#         * Rust ignore (BurntSushi) — DIRECT PARALLEL: wraps
#                                        walkdir (R641) with
#                                        gitignore + ignore-file
#                                        discovery
#         * Rust globset — different (pattern-matching only)
#         * Go src-d/go-git gitignore — separate gitignore parsing
#         * Python git-ls-tree — manual gitignore handling
#     globby is the SECOND documented Node.js Axis 14 library
#     providing high-level glob wrapper over fast-glob + built-in
#     gitignore + expand-directories + isGitIgnored helpers +
#     Sindre Sorhus four-library + chalk-org ecosystem provenance.
